This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it focuses on face and fingerprint verification, which are common applications in computer vision. Additionally, the paper proposes a deep learning model to address the challenges of verification, which is a common topic in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of generative and discriminative components in the proposed model also suggests a potential fit with the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve image data, which is a common type of data in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
